    "system.lanthanum.title": "Lanthanum",
    "system.lanthanum.desc": "The namesake of the lanthanide series, essential for hybrid car batteries and high-end camera lenses.",
    "system.lanthanum.details": "<b>Key Facts</b><br>• Chemical Symbol — La<br>• Atomic Number — 57<br>• Silvery-white, very soft rare earth metal<br>• First element of the lanthanide series<br>• Essential for NiMH batteries used in hybrid vehicles<br>• Name comes from Greek 'lanthanein' meaning to lie hidden<br>• Discovered in 1839 in Stockholm<br><br><b>Atomic Structure</b><br>• 57 protons in the nucleus<br>• 57 electrons surrounding the nucleus<br>• One stable natural isotope (Lanthanum-139)<br>• Electron Configuration — [Xe] 5d¹ 6s²<br>• Located in Period 6, Group 3 (Lanthanides)<br><br><b>Physical Properties</b><br>• Silvery-white color; malleable and ductile<br>• Boiling Point — 3464°C<br>• Melting Point — 918°C<br>• Hexagonal crystal structure at room temperature<br>• Soft enough to be cut with a knife<br>• High refractive index when used in glass<br><br><b>Chemical Properties</b><br>• One of the most reactive rare earth metals<br>• Rapidly oxidizes in air, forming a powdery layer<br>• Reacts with water to form La(OH)₃ and H₂<br>• Dissolves easily in dilute mineral acids<br>• Typical oxidation state — +3<br><br><b>Industrial Production</b><br>• Extracted mainly from monazite and bastnäsite minerals<br>• Separated from other rare earths by ion exchange or solvent extraction<br>• Metal produced by reducing fluoride with calcium<br><br><b>Applications</b><br>• Optics: High-refraction lenses for cameras and microscopes<br>• Energy: NiMH rechargeable batteries (hybrid car batteries)<br>• Petroleum: Fluid catalytic cracking (FCC) catalysts<br>• Lighting: Carbon arc electrodes for cinema projection<br>• Water: Phosphate removal in pools and aquariums",
    "system.lanthanum.fact": "Lanthanum makes up about 25% of the flint used in cigarette lighters (mischmetal).",
    "resource.wiki.lanthanum": "Wikipedia: Lanthanum",
    "resource.pubchem.lanthanum": "PubChem - Lanthanum",
    "ai.lanthanum.simple": "Lanthanum is element 57, a hidden metal that makes your phone battery last and camera photos sharp.",
    "ai.lanthanum.detailed": "Lanthanum oxide is used in optical glasses to improve refraction. It is also a key component in NiMH batteries.",
